    caption: [Life history of a red-spotted newt, *Notophthalmus viridescens* of the family Salamandridae. In many habitats the aquatic larva metamorphoses into a brightly colored “red eft” stage, which remains on land from 1 to 3 years before transforming into a secondarily aquatic adult.],
    path: "../fig/fig-2025-11-28-16-26-01.png"
